{"cursor":"9343","size":14,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n.]] The 'Disruption of 1843' was a schism within the established Church of\nScotland, in which 450 ministers of the Church broke away, over the issue of the\nChurch's relationship with the State, to form the Free Church of Scotland. It\ncame at the end of a bitter conflict within the established Church, and had huge\neffects not only within the Church, but also upon Scottish civic life.\n","linknr":159,"url":"Disruption_of_1843","recorded":1362671328,"links":19,"instances":["photographer","religion"],"pdf":[],"categories":["History of the Church of Scotland","Presbyterianism in Scotland","Schisms in Christianity","1843 in Scotland","19th-century Christianity","1843 in religion"],"headings":["The issues","The 'Ten Years' Conflict'","The Disruption","References","Bibliography","See also"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a4/Text_document_with_red_question_mark.svg/40px-Text_document_with_red_question_mark.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/38/Disruption_forming_Free_Kirk.jpg/350px-Disruption_forming_Free_Kirk.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1a/St._Andrew%27s_Church%2C_George_Street_Edinburgh.jpg/160px-St._Andrew%27s_Church%2C_George_Street_Edinburgh.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/Free_Church_of_Scotland_deed_of_demission_dsc05586.jpg/160px-Free_Church_of_Scotland_deed_of_demission_dsc05586.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Dumbarton_Presbytery_1845.jpg/200px-Dumbarton_Presbytery_1845.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits